venue.name: Aoringo (อะโอะรินโกะ)

tip.text: Brunch burger is quite excellent.
The wasabi prawn, which is supposed to be one of the chef's specialty, was really disappointing. The deep-fried prawns were no longer crispy by the time they reached our table.
Gyu enoki maki is interesting, but skip the scallop sashimi - too cold and not fresh enough.
Steaks have a weird, Maggie sauce, taste. But otherwise ok.

venue.name: MOF の My Izakaya, Japanese Casual Resturant & Cafe

tip.text: Crab cream croquette was surprisingly good. But service staff was brusque and disinterested in putting, moving and removing dishes on table.
Only organic ingredients used here. The fish is excellent.
The red curry is excellent, especially with the duck as the protein.
Tagliatelle with garlic and vegetables.
Try the Fried Chili Curry (with shrimp or meat) - absolutely delicious. Drunken fried noodles were good too.
Food is good, especially the grilled fish. But service was non-existent.
The deep-fried whole fish with garlic and chili is excellent - crispy yet tender.
Avoid the grilled shrimp on the Classic Caesar - not fresh!
